char is 1 byte (4 - 3)
int is 4 bytes (3 + 1)
float is 4 bytes (5 - 1)
variables 4 bytes (9 - 5)

when a variable is called, the computer finds creates the space needed as provided above and allocates a special address at random.

char 256 (2^8) because 8 is the number of bits

int 2^32 ^  (= to the power of)
